452.title: Shannon
452.text: The shannon (Sh) is a unit of [-3xd]. One shannon is the difference in [info_entropy entropy] between a [-probability_distribution] on a [-binary_variable] that assigns 50% to each value, and one that assigns 100% to one of the two values.
